==English==

===Etymology===
From [[point]] + [[-less]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-pointless.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''pointless''' (''[[comparative]]: '''more pointless'''; [[superlative]]: '''most pointless''''')
# Having no [[prominent]] or [[important]] feature, as of an [[argument]], [[discourse]], etc.; having no [[purpose]].
#: ''a '''pointless''' remark''
#: ''The [[sequel]] to the film was even more '''pointless''' than the original''
# Wanting [[keenness]]; having no well-defined [[termination]].
#: ''a '''pointless''' sword''

====Synonyms====
*[[blunt]], [[obtuse]], [[dull]], [[stupid]]


